Set-up

library(tidyverse)
library(forcats)

Ingest Species Data

surveys <- read_csv(
  here::here(
    "supporting_artifacts",
    'surveys.csv'
  )
)

1: Revisiting Lab 2

1. & 2.

surveys <- surveys |> 
  mutate(
    species = fct_reorder(
      species,
      weight,
      .fun = mean,
      .desc = TRUE
    )
  )
    
surveys |> 
  ggplot(
    mapping = aes(
      x = weight,
      y = species
    )
  ) +
    geom_jitter(color = 'tomato', alpha = 1/15) +
    geom_boxplot() +
# Question 2:
  labs(
    title = 'Species',
    xlab = 'Weight'
  ) +
  theme(
    axis.title.y = element_blank()
  )

2: Time-Series Plot

1.

surveys_ts <- surveys |> 
  group_by(
    genus,
    year
  )
  
ggplot(
  data = surveys_ts,
  mapping = aes(
    x = year,
    y = weight,
    color = genus
  )
) +
geom_line() +
labs(
  x = 'Year',
  y = 'Weight',
  color = 'Genus'
)

2.

surveys_ts_mean <- surveys_ts |> 
  mutate(
    avg_weight = mean(weight)
  )

ggplot(
  data = surveys_ts_mean,
  mapping = aes(
    x = year,
    y = avg_weight,
    color = genus
  )
) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(
    x = 'Year',
    y = 'Average Weight',
    color = 'Genus'
  )

3.

ggplot(
  data = surveys_ts_mean,
  mapping = aes(
    x = year,
    y = avg_weight,
    color = fct_reorder(
      genus,
      weight,
      .fun = mean,
      .desc = T
    )
  )
) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(
    x = 'Year',
    y = 'Average Weight',
    color = 'Genus'
  )

4.

ggplot(
  data = surveys_ts_mean,
  mapping = aes(
    x = year,
    y = avg_weight,
    color = fct_reorder(
      genus,
      weight,
      .fun = mean,
      .desc = T
    )
  )
) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(
    x = 'Year',
    title = 'Average Weight of Animals by Year',
    color = 'Genus of Animal'
  ) +
  theme(
    axis.title.y = element_blank()
  )

3: Captures over the Week

1.

rodents <- surveys |> 
  filter(
    taxa == 'Rodent',
    day_of_week != 'NA'
  )

ggplot(
  data = rodents,
  mapping = aes(
    x = day_of_week
  )
) +
  geom_bar()

2.

ggplot(
  data = rodents,
  mapping = aes(
    y = fct_relevel(
      day_of_week,
      'Sat',
      'Fri',
      'Thu',
      'Wed',
      'Tue',
      'Mon',
      'Sun'
    )
  )
) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(
    x = 'Number of Rodents',
    title = 'Number of Rodents Captured, by Day of Week'
  ) +
  theme(
    axis.title.y = element_blank()
  )

3.

ggplot(
  data = rodents,
  mapping = aes(
    y = fct_collapse(
      day_of_week,
      Weekend = c('Sun', 'Sat'),
      Weekday = c('Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri')
    )
  )
) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(
    x = 'Number of Rodents',
    title = 'Number of Rodents Captured, Weekend vs. Weekday'
  ) +
  theme(
    axis.title.y = element_blank()
  )
